latestIgtvVideos.title: STEP BY STEP✅
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hair colour DIY at home💯// This is literally how easy it was and if you have any doubts regarding the same, I’d love to chat in the comments with you✨

Hope this was helpful, do tag me if you try this and please share and save this video for later 🌹

Few things you should know:
-To wash- completely rinse off the colour and then shampoo and condition as per your normal routine with a colour protect shampoo 
-Colours and developers are Available at any beauty store or online 
- 20Vol is ideal for reds 
- My colour might be slightly brighter in appearance because I already have a lot of red pigments deposited in my hair and that’s why it may look lighter or different on yours.
- Reds mostly need Pre lightners to turn out extra bright 
- I used 1 and a half tubes for the length of my hair but you need to decide howmuch you need 
- Every colour technique has a different application method 
- this is my personal technique & however you may need a different one depending how which parts you want to colour, you can DM me and we can personally discuss this too

*DISCLAIMER* 
-DO NOT try if you’re allergic to colour or have any such allergies to any of these products (I won’t be responsible)

Recommended: take a little colour test if this is your first time, by depositing some colour and developer at the back of your ear (leave it on for 15 minutes) and if you have no reaction then youre good.

latestPosts.caption:
Do you agree with me? 😳 // This isn’t personal and neither do I think dettol hand wash is not a good product, it’s GREAT and has lived in my house since I’ve been a kid (and I’m sure in all your houses as well) it’s just NOT for your makeup brushes!!! 

It may ‘disinfect’ your brushes but it isn’t really cleaning them. What has shocked me the most is that I’ve seen makeup artists use dettol to clean their brushes 🤯

It’s so important for us as artists to keep our brushes ‘clean’ ‘disinfected’ and not carry forward product since it’s used on multiple faces , so none of these laundry soap bars and dish soaps are helping, they’re just accumulating all this extra harsh ingredient and causing a reaction (and you’ll never even know it was caused from your brushes) 😳

Use a face wash, a brush cleaner , even a makeup remover (in between cleints) if needed at all in an emergency hit STOP using products that you’ll NEVER use on your face to clean your brushes…. 

What’s are your thoughts? If you agree, I urge you to share this
